<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[804,1456,477,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis box="[842,899,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Notes</emphasis>
– A single collection was designated by Boissier (1867) in the protologue oF 
<emphasis box="[1136,1456,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="Balansa 1312" authorityName="Balansa" authorityYear="1312" box="[1136,1452,509,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="splendens">S. splendens (Balansa 1312)</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This collection clearly corresponds to two gatherings, one (in flowers) collected on 
<date box="[1077,1154,573,597]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="2015-07">July 15</date>
and a second (in Fruits) on 
<date box="[804,920,606,630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="1917-08">August 17</date>
(
<figureCitation box="[935,1001,605,630]" captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="3.[109,136,1308,1327]" captionTargetBox="[109,759,279,1293]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[107,760,278,1294]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. – Lectotype of Silene splendens Boiss. (designated by an arrow). [Balansa 1312, G-BOIS]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/162050/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Ŋese two gatherings have been widely distributed with a single label indicating both flowering and Fruiting dates. We consider that the most complete material is in flower and thereFore designate the specimen mounted on the leFt oF the First sheet at G-BOIS as the 
<typeStatus box="[1351,1454,733,757]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[812,876,765,790]" captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="3.[109,136,1308,1327]" captionTargetBox="[109,759,279,1293]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[107,760,278,1294]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. – Lectotype of Silene splendens Boiss. (designated by an arrow). [Balansa 1312, G-BOIS]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/162050/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). CareFul studies oF all material available allow separating the two gatherings in the relevant herbaria where the Fruiting material is designated as remaining 
<typeStatus box="[1275,1370,830,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">syntypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
